msgid "Discover how to verify and attest the integrity of your SL Micro system using the Keylime agent as a trusted third-party solution for remote attestation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remote attestation using Keylime"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter focuses on the remote attestation of &slema; using the <emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> agent."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: date
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid "2022-10-17"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "With the growing demand on securing devices against unauthorized changes, the use of the security mechanism called <emphasis>remote attestation (RA)</emphasis> has been experiencing significant growth. Using RA, a host (client) can authenticate its boot chain status and running software on a remote host (verifier). <emphasis>Remote attestation</emphasis> is usually combined with public-key encryption (by using TPM2), thus the sent information can only be read by the services that requested the attestation, and the validity of the data can be verified."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "Throughout this document, the following terms are used:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "Attestation key (AK)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "is a data signing key that proves that the data comes from a real TPM and has not been tampered with."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "Core root of trust for measurement"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "is a starting point of the boot process that cannot be altered and calculates the first hash of the layer above."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "Endorsement key (EK)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "is an encryption key that is permanently embedded in the TPM when it is manufactured. The public part of the key is used to recognize a genuine TPM."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Integrity management architecture (IMA)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "the kernel integrity subsystem that provides a means of detecting malicious changes to files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Measured boot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "in this method, each component in the booting sequence calculates a hash of the next one before delegating the execution of the next component. The hash extends one or several PCRs of the TPM. An event is created with the information about where the measurement took place and what was measured. Such events are collected in an event log, and, along with the extended PCR values, the events can be compared with the expected values representing a healthy system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Platform Configuration Register (PCR)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "is a memory location in TPM that, for example, stores hashes of booting layers. PCR can be updated only by using the non-reversible operation&mdash; <literal>extend</literal> . A signed list of current PCR values can be obtained by the <command>quote</command> command on TPM, and this quote can be verified by a third party during the attestation process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Secure boot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "each step of the booting process checks a cryptographic signature on the executable of the next step before launching it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trusted Platform Module (TPM)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "is a self-contained security cryptographic processor present in the system as hardware or implemented in the firmware that serves as a root of trust. TPM provides a PCR for storing the hashes of booting layers. A typical TPM provides several functions, like a random number generator, counters, or a local clock. It also stores 24 PCRs, grouped by banks per each supported cryptographic hash function (SHA1, SHA256, SHA384, or SHA512)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually, by default, TPM usage is disabled. Therefore, the measured boot does not take place. To enable the remote attestation, enable TPM in the EFI/BIOS menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "About <emphasis>Keylime</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> is a remote attestation solution that enables you to monitor the health of remote nodes using a TPM as a root of trust for measurement. With <emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> , you can perform several tasks like validation of the PCRs extended during the measured boot, analysis and assertions of the event log, assertion of the value of any PCR in the remote system, and also monitoring the validity of open or executed files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> also provides a framework for delivering encrypted data to verified nodes. This data is the so-called payload. The framework can also execute custom scripts that are triggered when a machine fails the attested measurements."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> consists of an agent, a verifier, a registrar, and a command-line tool (tenant). Agents are on those systems that need to be attested. The verifier and registrar are on remote systems that perform the registration and attestation of agents. Keep in mind that only the agent role is available on &slema;. For details about each component, refer to the following sections."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:159
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> agent"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "The agent is a service that runs on the system that needs to be attested. The agent sends the event log, IMA hashes, and information about the measured boot to the verifier, using the local TPM as a certifier of the data validity."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "When a new agent is started, the agent needs to register itself in the registrar first. To do so, the agent needs a TLS certificate to establish the connection. The TLS certificate is generated by the registrar, but it needs to be installed manually to the agent. After the registration, the agent sends its attestation key and the public part of the endorsement key to the registrar. The registrar responds to the agent with a challenge in a process called credential activation, which will validate the TPM of the agent. Once the agent has been registered, it is ready to be enrolled for attestation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> registrar"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "The registrar is used to register agents that should be attested. The registrar collects the agent's attestation key, the public part of the endorsement key and the endorsement key certification, and verifies that the agent attestation key belongs to the endorsement key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Keylime</emphasis> verifier"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:189
#, no-c-format
msgid "The verifier performs the actual attestation of agents and continuously pulls the required attestation data from agents (amongst others, the PCR values, IMA logs, and UEFI event logs)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_security_attestation.xml:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting up the verifier and registrar"
msgstr ""

